02/06/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan met with Pakistani counterpart Shaukat Aziz on Wednesday (1 June). They agreed to boost bilateral trade co-operation as well as collaboration in the defence sector. According to Aziz, they would seek to raise trade volume -- now at around $400m -- more than twofold, to $1 billion. Sources say they also discussed the joint production of tanks and other military vehicles. (Daily Times - 02/06/05; TurkishPress.com - 01/06/05)
